generalComment.value:
"•Phase A1 quantity of materials present in the concrete recipes and in the bills of materials of the products considered. 
•Phase A2: supplier addresses
•Phase A3: quantities relating to emissions into the atmosphere, auxiliary materials and plant waste
The type of material, the manufacturing processes of the raw materials and waste treatment have been selected from the Ecoinvent database 3.8.
The supply of electricity takes place through the national energy system
(modeled considering the Italian Residual Energy Mix 2021 - Source AIB) and from a photovoltaic system placed on the roof of the factory (modeled as a 3kWp photovoltaic with multi-Si cells).
The supply of thermal energy (methane gas) takes place through the national energy system (modeled as heat from natural gas burnt in industrial furnace > 100KW).
Proxy data, for an overall impact of less than 0.01% of the total, was used for the following auxiliary materials: heat pipe cleaning additive, rust inhibitor, putty, colorant for exposed concrete finishes.
Generic data were used by applying criteria of geographical equivalence, technology and with respect to system boundaries, considering information between 2010 and 2020."


"Made on the basis of the volumes of concrete processed in the batching plant relating to the year 2022."


The exclusions for which the relative environmental impact along the life cycle of the products is considered negligible are employee travel, ordinary and extraordinary maintenance.                                                                                                 Cut off includes galvanizing of the metal components, hand-painted minium through cans, non-conveyed emissions due to welding processes and the primary packaging of finished products.

technologicalApplicability.value:
Pillars are linear vertical structural elements of a building, made of reinforced concrete. They are sized and designed in accordance with current technical regulations to resist design stresses and transmit them to the ground through the foundation structures. These elements have CE markings in accordance with the CPR 305/2011 with reference to the specific harmonized standard EN13225:2013.
 This study regards the average product of the pillars which are prefabricated in the production site in Carvico (BG).
